Context: This course is a degree preparation program focused on health science disciplines, held at George Brown College's St. James "A" building located at 200 King Street East. The duration and start dates are yet to be determined. Students will study concepts in chemistry for biological studies and delve into areas such as biochemistry, metabolic processes, homeostasis, and molecular genetics. For more information about the U-Level Bridging program, contact gbcdegreebridging@georgebrown.ca or call (416) 415-5000 ext. 3683. George Brown College has signed an articulation agreement with 14 participating colleges for English language proficiency requirements in diploma programs. For application deadlines, college news, and events, sign up on their website or contact ask.george@georgebrown.ca using the provided phone number or visiting their social media hub. The information contained in this website is subject to change without notice.
